item: Politoys Magic Cube (Bűvös Kocka), Hungarian
itemGradeDescription: Possibly used but must appear to be new
boxGradeDescription: Possibly used but must appear to be new
notes: I speculate that this was a short-run production where Politoys was experimenting with printing their own boxes using the new, low cost IBM 3800-3 laserxerographic printer, which debuted in 1982 and was commercially available in late 1984. The 3800-3 was the first printer to allow licensing of Sonoran Sans, a "functional equivalent of Monotype Arial", at a much lower cost of Linotype's Helvetica, making it a lucrative investment for smaller printhouses. Alternatively, this item may be counterfeited.
